§ Definition ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ Suppose $x ∈ 𝗥$ is a real number. ⦉

  ‖ The ❬lower integer part❭ (or ❬floor❭) of $x$ is the largest
    integer $a ∈ 𝗭$ satisfiying $a ≤ x$. ⦉

  ‖ Similarly the ❬upper integer part❭ of $x$ is the smallest
    integer $b ∈ 𝗭$ such that $x ≤ b$ ⦉
⦉

§ Notation ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ Suppose $x ∈ 𝗥$. We denote the lower and upper integer
    parts of $x$ by
    ◇ ⦊
      ‖ \floor{x} \quad \text{ and } \quad \ceil{x} ⦉
    ⦉
    respectively. ⦉
⦉

